# style editors with tailwind classes or scoped style tags

Two styling approaches for editors:

1. **Tailwind classes** — Preferred. Apply utility classes directly to elements.
2. **Scoped style tags** — When Tailwind is insufficient. Make selectors specific to the editor component to prevent global CSS leakage.

```tsx
// ✅ Tailwind
<div className="flex gap-4 p-6 rounded-lg border">

// ✅ Scoped style tag
<style>{`
  .my-editor-name .custom-table { border-collapse: collapse; }
  .my-editor-name .custom-table td { padding: 8px; }
`}</style>

// ❌ Unscoped — will affect the entire app
<style>{`
  table { border-collapse: collapse; }
  td { padding: 8px; }
`}</style>
```

